               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origDate>15th century</origDate>
                     <origPlace>
                        <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100036">Italy</placeName>
                     </origPlace>. The coat of arms found on the remains of the original cover may point to an owner from neapolitan royal family, cf. <bibl>
                        <title ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107162" type="short">Marinis (1952-1957)</title>
                        <citedRange unit="volume" from="2" to="2"/>
                        <citedRange unit="page" from="71" to="71"/>
                     </bibl>.
                        </origin>
                  <provenance>Owner signature on <locus from="1r" to="1r" scheme="folios"/> probably points to Antonino Amico (1586-1641), canon and historian in Palermo. The last known owner, the book collector <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102522">Per Hierta</persName> (1864-1924), has signed his name on <locus from="L1r" to="L1r" scheme="folios"/>.</provenance>
                  <acquisition>The manuscript was included among the parts of Per Hierta's collection that were donated to the <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100004">National Library</orgName> in the first part of the 20th century.</acquisition>
               </history>
